## Folder Structure

- `/drafts` — Active work-in-progress.
- `/references` — Domain knowledge and source material.
- `/sessions` — Timestamped session logs for continuity.
- `/final` — Polished output ready for handoff.
- `/archive` — Retired or superseded work.
- `REFLECTIONS.md` — Lessons learned and mistakes to avoid repeating.

## Routing Table

| Task | Go To | Read |
|------|-------|------|
| Start new work | `/sessions` | `drafts/CONTEXT.md` then create a session file |
| Continue existing work | `/sessions` | Most recent session file, then `REFLECTIONS.md` |
| Look up domain knowledge | `/references` | Relevant reference file |
| Finalize output | `/final` | `drafts/CONTEXT.md` for the handoff process |
| Review past decisions | `/archive` | `REFLECTIONS.md` |

